  "why": "The paper explicitly designs and enforces semantic-preserving and naturalness-preserving mechanisms throughout the fuzzing / optimization process. AutoDAN initializes from handcrafted prototype prompts and uses LLM-based diversification and mutation that are intended to \"preserve the inherent logical flow and meaning\" of prompts, applies low-rate controlled mutation (pmutation = 0.01), uses elitism and hierarchical (sentence- and paragraph-level) operators to avoid destructive drift, and measures stealthiness with perplexity (PPL). The method also keeps the malicious question Q fixed while optimizing the jailbreak prompt J, i.e., it mutates prompt text only, not the semantic target. Empirical evidence (PPL comparisons, robustness to perplexity/paraphrasing defenses) further shows the mutants remain realistic and semantically meaningful. These design choices satisfy the metric's High criteria (semantic consistency where required and explicit naturalness preservation).",
